news.title: China's Wanda Group unit raises $300 million in second dollar bond issue this year
news.para: Wanda Properties Global Co Ltd's latest three-year bond was finalised with a yield of 12.375% and coupon of 11%, according to a term sheet and a company presentation seen by Reuters. The deal came after the $400 million sale of a two-year bond in mid-January.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board slashes transfer fee for commercial properties
news.para: The transfer fees of commercial properties that were sold by the CHB through a competitive bidding process (auction/tender) for the pending and new applications have been on the lines of the estate office.

news.title: Vigilance bureau begins probe into LIT's prime land auction in 2021 in Ludhiana
news.para: In his complaint, Tikka has sought action against former LIT chairman Raman Balasubramaniyam, other LIT officials and Ritesh property that had purchased the land in an e-auction.

news.title: Three state governments slow in executing rural housing scheme
news.para: The aim of the scheme is to provide pucca houses with basic amenities to all those living in kutcha and dilapidated houses in rural areas and the states have a target of handing over the houses within a stipulated time.

news.title: February 20 deadline for property taxpayers to file objections: Nashik civic body
news.para: NMC will continue with the property tax as is, if property owners do not take objections. Moreover, the property owners have to pay all their property tax dues by March 31 before filing objections.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body slashes cheque bounce penalty for commercial property tax
news.para: ​​Earlier, the civic body used to charge 5% of the tax bill amount or Rs 1,000, whichever is higher. Now, the AMC will charge 5% of the tax bill amount or Rs 1,000, whichever is less.

news.title: Kolhapur: Over 60,000 property owners to gain from property tax fine waiver
news.para: There are 1.45 lakh properties in Kolhapur city. Owners of over 60,000 properties have dues over Rs25 crore excluding the fine, which is levied at 2% for every month of delay in payment.

news.title: UP-RERA has disposed 41% of total disputes: Rajive Kumar, Chairman
news.para: UP-RERA will soon start grading projects and developers based on various parameters like financial quality, organizational structure, certifications, track records, compliance adherence and customer feedback, said Rajive Kumar, chairman.

news.title: Mohali development body to auction 77 properties, total reserve price is Rs 2,100 crore
news.para: Punjab housing and urban development minister Aman Arora said the total reserve price of all the properties stands at Rs 2,100 crore.

news.title: SC restrains construction within core areas in tiger reserves, national parks, wildlife sanctuaries
news.para: The top court was dealing with a matter raising issues such as alleged illegal constructions in tiger reserves and the establishment of a tiger safari in the buffer area of Corbett Tiger Reserve in Uttarakhand.

news.title: Chargeable FSI to bring in additional Rs 500 crore for Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: The FSI refers to the ratio between a plot's built-up area to the actual plot area on which the building is constructed. The builders buy FSI from the civic body's town planning department above the basic base FSI available to them to add more floors to their existing structures.

news.title: Manesar scam: Allottees, investors ask for detachment of properties
news.para: The ED had attached these properties under a money laundering case that was registered in Chandigarh and linked to the Central Bureau of Investigation’s September 2015 case where the builders and politicians had allegedly committed a scam to the tune of Rs 1,500 crore in the garb of land acquisition.

news.title: Occupancy certificate not needed for deemed conveyance in Maharashtra
news.para: However, the facility comes with a rider, wherein the housing society is required to submit a self-declaration form, affirming that it would pay the necessary dues and get OC from the local authority later.

news.title: NGT imposes Rs 113 crore environmental compensation on Wave City's builder
news.para: These agencies were asked to carry out a probe after a Ghaziabad resident had filed a petition in the NGT, alleging the Wave Group flouted environmental norms ranging from groundwater extraction to cutting trees and violated solid waste management (SWM) laws as well.

news.title: Survey on illegal colonies in Sohna begins, 12 found so far
news.para: Mushrooming of illegal colonies in Sohna and nearby areas is posing a challenge to the civic authorities in developing infrastructure and amenities for newly created sectors.
